HEADWORD: Thryfallow
<hw>Thry"fal`low</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps fr.
<ets>thrice + fallow</ets>. Cf. <er>Trifallow</er>.]</ety> <def>To plow
for the third time in summer; to trifallow.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>thrifallow</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Tusser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

